data.description: Rare Triple lot, 120 feet of waterfront, gulf access, 4 bedroom home on the beautiful and sought after 8 Lakes. It has a stunning water view and desirable southern pool exposure! The home has suffered roof damage from hurricane Ian that allowed some rainwater to come through and caused sheetrock damage on some ceilings, and baseboard damage. The elevation is high enough that seawater never entered the house. The kitchen and interior living spaces were remodeled prior to the storm. The kitchen has beautiful granite countertops, and solid wood cabinets. This home would be move-in ready with a new roof, attic insulation, and sheetrock repairs.   A big part of the work for a new roof has already been done. The property is priced accordingly discounting the hurricane damage.  Another great option is to build a large estate home here and take advantage of the unique 120-feet of waterfront on this 1/3 acre premium lot on the 8 lakes offering quick Gulf access. This must see, rare 33% larger property with spectacular water views on the much sought after 8 lakes, offers a unique opportunity for home ownership for boaters, and anyone that enjoys a beautiful water view.
